VPIF Sample applications
========================

Sample applications demonstrating VPIF capabilities.


Building the sample applications
--------------------------------

make KERNEL_PATH=<kernel directory path>


VPIF MMAP based sample application
----------------------------------

Options:
	-c <channel-> 0: Composite or 1: S-Video>
	-p <0: no prints or 1:print frame number>
	-m <0:NTSC or 1:PAL>
	-s <stress test: 0 or 1>

To test NTSC composite
./vpif_test_mmap_loopback -c0 -m0  -p1

To test PAL composite
./vpif_test_mmap_loopback -c0 -m1  -p1

To test NTSC S-Video
./vpif_test_mmap_loopback -c1 -m0  -p1

To test PAL S-Video
./vpif_test_mmap_loopback -c1 -m1  -p1

By default the test runs for 500 frames, unless the stress test option is set
(with -s1 option) in which case the application does not exit.


VPIF User pointer based sample application
------------------------------------------

Options:
	-c <channel-> 0: Composite or 1: S-Video>
	-p <0: no prints or 1:print frame number>
	-m <0:NTSC or 1:PAL>
	-s <stress test: 0 or 1>

To test NTSC composite
./vpif_test_userptr_loopback -c0 -m0  -p1

To test PAL composite
./vpif_test_userptr_loopback -c0 -m1  -p1

To test NTSC S-Video
./vpif_test_userptr_loopback -c1 -m0  -p1

To test PAL S-Video
./vpif_test_userptr_loopback -c1 -m1  -p1

By default the test runs for 500 frames, unless the stress test option is set
(with -s1 option) in which case the application does not exit.


VPIF display(color bar)sample application
------------------------------------------

Options:
	-o <output number-> 0: Composite or 1: S-Video>
	-p <0: no prints or 1:print frame number>
	-m <0:NTSC or 1:PAL>

To test NTSC composite
./vpif_test_display -o0 -m0  -p1

To test PAL composite
./vpif_test_display -o0 -m1  -p1

To test NTSC S-Video
./vpif_test_display -o1 -m0  -p1

To test PAL S-Video
./vpif_test_display -o1 -m1  -p1

Please note that the bootargs for NTSC and PAL have to be set properly
for the sample applications to execute.
